text.__SUMMARY__: Psilocybe keralensis is a species of psilocybin mushroom in the family Strophariaceae. It contains the compounds psilocybin and psilocin. Psilocybe keralensis is known only from Kerala, India. It is in the Psilocybe fagicola complex with Psilocybe fagicola, Psilocybe oaxacana, Psilocybe banderillensis, Psilocybe columbiana, Psilocybe herrerae, Psilocybe neoxalapensis, and Psilocybe teofiloi.
